Body: What is holding the crypto market back?  According to Forbes, some of the reasons why the cryptocurrency market can’t reach its full potential are:  1 The interconnection of coin prices that make risk management almost impossible – if one asset in the portfolio drops, likely all others will too; 2 High amount of ICO scams; 3 Limited ways of making profit that are becoming less and less effective; 4 Lack of strategy when it comes to return on investment predictions. 5 The inability of crypto exchanges to provide adequate liquidity.  Despite the problems, millions of people are getting into the crypto market and with the focus on real-world application, stability and adoption we are sure to see our field succeed in the long run.  https://www.forbes.com/sites/geraldfenech/2019/01/17/what-is-plaguing-the-cryptocurrency-market/#474e01774edf

Title: [ANN][FEB19] AB-CHAIN.com - Ads in BlockChain
Body: Why are cryptocurrencies so volatile?  Cryptocurrency market fluctuations by tens of percents daily, but what exactly makes it so unstable in comparison to the traditional fiat market?  Firstly the market is less than a decade old, and fluctuations are natural. Lack of liquidity compared to the traditional market, relatively low daily trading volumes and a massive gain of new adopters who influence the market with their investments every day are some of the most significant factors, according to the article by Toshi Times.  It is likely that as the crypto market matures, it will stabilize, opening new possibilities for real-world use of cryptocurrencies!  https://toshitimes.com/how-do-cryptocurrency-prices-work/

Title: [ANN][FEB19] AB-CHAIN.com - Ads in BlockChain
Body: AB-CHAIN MARKET NEWS Belarusian Ministry Of Finance Releases Cryptocurrency Accounting Framework  Belarus has officially introduced cryptocurrency accounting standards, according to a March 6 document by the Ministry of Finance. The document lays out the information needed about tokens for accounting purposes, as well as how to categorize tokens received by organizations depending on their further use.  Belarus has been super liberal and supportive regarding cryptocurrency. In November last year, crypto-related bill for the Belarusian High-Tech Park was signed, allowing new technologies to develop specifically including cryptocurrencies and Initial Coin Offerings(ICO).  It's interesting that cryptocurrency will be put on organizations' account as credit  Cryptocurrecy market still has further way to go, which means there is potential to grow.

Author: Jack.AB-CHAIN
Title: [ANN][FEB19] AB-CHAIN.com - Ads in BlockChain
Body: Prk_7, thank you for your question!  Cryptocurrency advertising market is still only forming and there is a lot of opportunities for new companies to arise in this space. And along those companies, AB-CHAIN is showing great traction, since we already have a working beta version, clients and revenue. That's before crowdfunding has even started!  We never relied on advertising on Facebook very heavily, so their ban on ICO ads will benefit us more than harm - More clients will come to our network.  We are developing AI that will revolutionize advertising for advertisers. Our technology aims to boost conversion into leads, rather than simply into clicks, and therefore we aim to give a significant upgrade to the overall effectiveness of campaigns.

Title: [ANN][FEB19] AB-CHAIN.com - Ads in BlockChain

Author: Jack.AB-CHAIN
Title: [ANN][FEB19] AB-CHAIN.com - Ads in BlockChain
Body: AB-CHAIN Weekly Report February 5–11  In weekly reports, we tell about the progress accomplished in the development of the AB-CHAIN ad network in the past seven days!  1. We have changed the AB-CHAIN token name to — RTB, which stands for “Real Time Bidding.” Soon we will update the name on the website and in the whitepaper. RTB is going to be the official code of AB-CHAIN token from now onwards.  2. We have published RTB token smart contract in Ethereum blockchain. The token smart-contract contains the combustion functionality. We also provided the possibility of simple migration to another contract to allow easy update of the token once the majority of the supply has been burned.  3. We successfully purchased advertising with RTB tokens as well as applied 50% commission burning mechanism on our test network. We plan to introduce these features in the live version of the network next week. Despite AB-CHAIN being in an early stage, the network is already becoming fully-featured!  We hope that you found this report useful. Follow our social media and stay updated on AB-CHAIN progress!

Author: Jack.AB-CHAIN
Title: [ANN][FEB19] AB-CHAIN.com - Ads in BlockChain
Body: Hello everyone! It is time for another AB-CHAIN weekly report!  Weekly Report Jan. 22-28  In weekly reports, we describe the progress achieved in the development of the AB-CHAIN ad network in the past week!  1. We have launched marketing campaigns of our first advertisers putting our growing network of publishers to good use! Many crowdfunded projects only claim to launch their products in late 2018, and AB-CHAIN already has a working business!  2. We have connected several new publishers, almost doubling the size of our network. The capacity is growing. We can attract more advertisers and provide the necessary amount of impressions.  3. We gained flexibility by supporting text ads. Now we can work with any website template which will help to connect large publishers, while advertisers do not have to tailor their ad designs to match our banners sizes.  We hope that you found this report useful. If you have any questions please, let us know and we will be happy to assist you!

Author: Jack.AB-CHAIN
Title: [ANN][FEB19] AB-CHAIN.com - Ads in BlockChain
Body: AB-CHAIN Weekly Report January 15 – 21 In weekly reports, we describe the progress achieved in the development of the AB-CHAIN ad network in the past week!  1. We have connected the first advertiser to the AB-CHAIN network and started actively attracting new advertisers!  2. Having received feedback about the advertiser’s office from the connected advertiser, we improved the cabinet. In particular, we made ad creation process significantly more intuitive by updating the UI.  3. We conducted tests of the DSP/SSP hub where we plan to buy and sell traffic and made a decision to start the integration to automate interactions between our platforms.  4. We continued to grow the AB-CHAIN catalog by connecting new publishers. Additionally, we have developed a solution for non-standard cases of bot traffic and click fraud.  5. We created the functionality that allows for internal payments from advertiser to publisher in AB-CHAIN Tokens, adding further incentive for advertisers to join AB-CHAIN by lowering the commission to 10% when payment is made in AB-CHAIN tokens. An average market commission is 20%.  We hope that you found this report useful. Stay in touch so we can watch how AB -CHAIN is developing week by week together!

Author: Jack.AB-CHAIN
Title: [ANN][FEB19] AB-CHAIN.com - Ads in BlockChain
Body: Hello retampan!  1 You do not have to exchange your BTC or ETH to purchase ad placements on the AB-CHAIN platform, but doing so will lower the platform commission from the market standard 20% to 10%, so it gives a 50% discount, essentially.  2 Yes, publishers will be able to withdraw earnings in fiat, as well as in cryptocurrency of their choice, but fiat withdrawal will be implemented in the second iteration of the platform, after all legal aspects will be ironed out.  3 CPM means Cost Per 1000 Impressions, which basically means that advertiser pays a certain amount when publisher generates 1000 impressions for him. This is a model that AB-CHAIN uses. CPL means Cost Per Lead, it defines how much revenue a publisher receives when he creates a lead for an advertiser. CPC is a Cost Per Click, which means that a publisher receives money each time a user clicks on the banner. CPO means Cost Per Order - so a publisher receives money only if a lead he or she generated performs some targeted actions of the advertiser’s website or platform.

Author: Jack.AB-CHAIN
Title: [ANN][FEB19] AB-CHAIN.com - Ads in BlockChain
Body: Weekly Report January 08 - 14  In weekly reports, we tell you about the progress accomplished in the development of the AB-CHAIN ad network in the last week!  1. We kept on actively connecting new publishers and growing the capacity of the network.  2. We have finished and finalized the integration with SendSay mailing service. The integration will allow us to save time by automating some of our communication processes.  3. We have completed the development of the advertiser’s cabinet in which advertisers can create campaigns using AB-CHAIN platform’s interface and purchase ad placements.  4. We completed the network workability tests and tested the mechanism of working with advertisers. This week we are ready to connect first paying advertisers.  5. We made an agreement with several partner DSP and SSP networks about traffic exchange tests.  Stay with us on our journey so we can watch how AB — CHAIN is progressing week by week together!

Author: AB-CHAIN_CEO
Title: [ANN][FEB19] AB-CHAIN.com - Ads in BlockChain
Body: Hey! Thanks for the question.  Let me explain how we differ from other projects using as example AdEx ICO.  (1) First of all we are focused on business and customers, so we do the product for advertisers first of all (because they are the paying customers), then for publishers and ad networks (helping them to adopt new technology). (2) AB-CHAIN is solving different problem than AdEx. AdEx (and several other ICOs) are addressing "Lack of consumer consent" and "Privacy concerns and data misuse". We solve the problem of accessing big volume of ad space being natively paid in cryptocurrency. (3) Technologically AB-CHAIN will not write ad stats to blockchain to prevent "Ad fraud" and avoid "Central regulation". We think that this is an unnecessary load on infrastructure that will not help to prevent fraud nor solve any regulatory problem, but will cost a lot for advertisers. (4) AB-CHAIN focuses on business development and we plan to spread our solution to b2b market (existing ad networks), allowing other players to earn, thus helping them to start accepting "magic" cryptocurrency. (5) Finally we are building ad network on basis of AB-CHAIN ERC20 coin used as a utility token inside of the platform. We also will be contributing to our clients (advertisers and publishers) and community. 5% from each transaction will be burned.

Author: AB-CHAIN_CEO
Title: [ANN][FEB19] AB-CHAIN.com - Ads in BlockChain
Body: Thanks a lot for reaching out and pointing at BAT. This is a marvelous concept we liked from the first glance!  AB-CHAIN on the other hand is different from BAT as far as AB-CHAIN is serving mostly ICO companies.  (1) First of all we are focused on business and customers, so we do the product for advertisers first of all (because they are the paying customers), then for publishers and ad networks (helping them to adopt new technology). (2) AB-CHAIN is solving different problem than BAT. BAT are addressing "Fraud and Malvertising", "Privacy concerns" and tiredness of customers of annoying ads. We solve the problem of accessing big volume of ad space being natively paid in cryptocurrency. (3) AB-CHAIN focuses on business development and we plan to spread our solution to b2b market (existing ad networks), allowing other players to earn, thus helping them to start accepting "magic" cryptocurrency. (4) Finally we are building profitable coin that will guarantee that paying for advertising services in advance, an advertiser will be able to get more than actually paid - due to coin price growth. Especially for this we build mechanism that will press the price of the ABC coin. Our goal is to give them access to huge market of traditional advertising that is now already holding attention of existing customers today.

Body: Belarus Cuts Taxes For Crypto Companies  Taxes for crypto-businesses are cut by the Belarus government to promote the development of tech and financial startups.  Belarus government has passed new statutes focused partly on promoting the development of companies that incorporate cryptocurrency and blockchain.  In accordance with the state-owned media agency BelTA, on Dec. 22 Belarus President Alexander Lukashenko signed a digital economy development decree that constitutionally enshrines the use of rising technologies like blockchain. The decree also offers major tax incentives to interest business activity.  The decree, as summarized by a Belarus IT firm that supported the legislation, boosts development of the country's High-Tech Park, an economic zone the government wants to present as a hub for tech and financial startups.  Source: https://www.coindesk.com/belarus-government-cuts-taxes-crypto-businesses/

Body: Israel Might Ban Public Firms from Bitcoin Trading  Israeli bitcoin trading companies are likely to face tighter rules forced by the country's finance regulator.  By Reuters, in a business conference on Dec. 26, the head the Israel Securities Authority (ISA) Shmuel Hauser promised to present a proposal to the ISA board next week, which will attempt to ban any company with a major involvement in bitcoin trading from the Tel Aviv Stock Exchange (TASE).  Hauser stated:  "If we have a company [and] their main business is digital currencies, we would not allow it. If already listed, its trading will be suspended."  According to Hauser, if the proposal is signed, it would have to go through a public hearing before the domestic exchange is required to abide the new laws.  Source: https://www.coindesk.com/israeli-finance-watchdog-seeks-ban-public-firms-bitcoin-trading/

Body: Find out what AB-CHAIN team has accomplished in the last seven days.  1. The development of the minimally viable version of the website where both advertisers and publishers will be registering their accounts is complete. The code was passed for internal testing. The functions include: Creation of the marketing campaign, which includes setting a budget, selecting audience targeting and site topics, uploading promotional visual materials and adding advertisement texts. Balance replenishment. Currently, the balance can be topped up with Ethereum, but we are working on accepting the AB-CHAIN token as well. The Review of analytics of all campaigns.  2. The publisher’s account is currently undergoing internal alpha testing, and is being prepared for the live tests on the market.  3. Having received the feedback from publishers, we are continuing the development of the AB-CHAIN widget. We are also working on the interface which will allow publishers to review statistics of the installed widgets as well as keep track of incoming payments and payment history.  4. We are conducting a live test of the AB-CHAIN token burning mechanism that makes use of the blockchain technology.  5. Additionally, we have integrated Sendsay mailing service, which will simplify and automate communication with AB-CHAIN clients and investors and allow to direct even more efforts to product development. We hope that you found this report useful. Stay with us on our journey, so we can watch how AB — CHAIN is progressing week by week together! If you have any questions, you can always contact us at team@ab-chain.com. We will be happy to assist you!

Author: AB-CHAIN_CEO
Title: [ANN][FEB19] AB-CHAIN.com - Ads in BlockChain
Body: Hey everybody! During one especially wintery cold Russian evening, the AB-CHAIN team ( or the part of the team that's based in Russia anyway ) was having some tea and thinking; we tell you everything we do as a company, but we also want you to get to know us as individuals... As people.  So, there it is! We will be posting something personal about each of our team members on a weekly basis so that you can discover something new about people, behind the AB-CHAIN ad network!  Let's start with our CEO Vladimir!  Vladimir was born and raised in a city of Perm, which is located on a very eastern side of European Russia. He has decided to become a developer and led several IT projects in his hometown, before choosing to move to Moscow about 8 and a half years ago.  Vladimir loves running! He participated in several worldwide mountain running events and marathons, including the Adidas Elbrus World Race 2017 and Marathon Du Mont Blanc 2017– one of the most scenic runs in the world.  He also loves China! Vladimir believes that commercially China will become one of the leading nations in the not so distant future, but apart from that, he hugely enjoys the culture and likes spending his holidays in this unique and special country.

Body: "Ethereum is one step closer to becoming a ""world computer""?  This December a new TrueBit protocol is being released. It is promising to remove the ""gas limit"" that at the current time puts an upper-bound on the number of computations the network can achieve. TrueBit is going to bring the second largest blockchain by market capitalization closer to its oft-touted goal of becoming a ""world computer.""  TrueBit is explicitly geared towards heavy computations which are required, for example, for video broadcasting and machine learning, promising to resolve the fact that ethereum is still about as fast as a ""smartphone from 1999,"" as ethereum creator Vitalik Buterin joked last year.  Source https://www.coindesk.com/world-computer-new-protocol-supercharge-ethereums-blockchain/

Author: AB-CHAIN_CEO
Title: [ANN][FEB19] AB-CHAIN.com - Ads in BlockChain
Body: Hello dear Candice,  Definitely we have a good team and experience, and it is exactly relevant to the project, yes, and brilliant advisors, we think that we could be one of the best teams at the market for such a solution.  Here is the analysis of the difference of AB-CHAIN and AdEx product: (1) First of all we are focused on business and customers, so we do the product for advertisers first of all (because they are the paying customers), then for publishers and ad networks (helping them to adopt new technology). (2) AB-CHAIN is solving different problem than AdEx. AdEx are addressing "Lack of consumer consent" and "Privacy concerns and data misuse". We solve the problem of accessing big volume of ad space being natively paid in cryptocurrency. (3) Technologically AB-CHAIN will not write ad stats to blockchain to prevent "Ad fraud" and avoid "Central regulation". We think that this is an unnecessary load on infrastructure that will not help to prevent fraud nor solve any regulatory problem, but will cost a lot for advertisers. Also it is necessary to mention that the fraud problem already has solutions and they work good, so there is nothing to do with blockchain here, we think it is unnecessary synthetic use of blockchain. (4) AB-CHAIN focuses on business development and we plan to spread our solution to b2b market (existing ad networks), allowing other players to earn, thus helping them to start accepting "magic" cryptocurrency. (5) Finally we are building profitable coin that will guarantee that paying for advertising services in advance, an advertiser will be able to get more than actually paid - due to coin price growth. Especially for this we build mechanism that will press the price of the ABC coin.  And one more, but this could be not the last. We have not raised millions of USD yet but have already started the first version of our product.

Author: rainbow169
Title: [ANN][FEB19] AB-CHAIN.com - Ads in BlockChain
Body: A few questions would appreciate your answers.  Will the business mainly be an advertising agency that accepts crytocurrency compared to the traditional agency? What is the inventory size and uniques that you have access to? What will be the advantage for companies to go through your channel rather than to convert cryto to fiat and then go through standard marketing channel?

Author: AB-CHAIN_CEO
Title: [ANN][FEB19] AB-CHAIN.com - Ads in BlockChain
Body: Hey, rainbow169! Good questions indeed!  Quote Will the business mainly be an advertising agency that accepts crytocurrency compared to the traditional agency?  This is a very felicitous remark, that this business in fact is both - platform and agency. Why platform: 1) after some customer development we know that traditional publishers do not understand cryptocurrency AT ALL - nor technology or mechanics, neither advantages; for the publisher it's just one more e-money like webmoney or paypal; 2) to fetch publisher's needs we have to provide full service - but first of all payment so that it will significantly lower the barrier that will allow one to start accepting cryptocurrency; 3) AND - that is even more important - the ability flawlessly to convert to fiat (yes, most - maybe 70 to 90% will convert to fiat right after receiving the crypto- earnings).  On the other hand correct tactics to go into agency's customer development is a bad strategy. Our vision is that "agency role" will be kept until we finish customer development with the first 10 to 20 clients-publishers. After that this will be given up to our ad networks partners as a b2b service to which we will provide payment service.  Quote What is the inventory size and uniques that you have access to?  We have some experience working with traffic of huge corporations (at the moment I own https://bonus.qiwi.com service and also work with other traffic of this company). And some connections besides QIWI that we will definitely use. But I think that our main goal is different - to build the product and value proposition that will drive to us more publishers to make much wider spread.  Quote What will be the advantage for companies to go through your channel rather than to convert cryto to fiat and then go through standard marketing channel?  1) Ease of use Why would you need to make additional step (conversion) if the same publisher will accept both cryptocurrency and fiat? 2) Cheaper price in cryptocurrency: + no conversion commission; + no slip in conversion (especially a problem if you convert $1m+); 3) Even cheaper price using ABC coin - 10% more advertising for the same money paid (we give up half of our commission); 4) If you decide to use ABC coin then you can buy it in advance and then get more advertising due to coin's price growth (reduction of money supply by burning the coin - we burn half our our commission received if paid in ABC); 5) Later on we will provide automatic conversion to those publishers that still do not accept cryptocurrency. In fact this is again the ease of use because in economic aspect this will not give additional cost effectiveness, but just one step less to do. I believe that easy and good products win the market just like iPhone.
